 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Data Science and Analytics - Online Adjunct, Undergraduate Level University of the Sciences in Philadelphia 24 reviews Philadelphia, PA 19104 Remote University of the Sciences in Philadelphia 24 reviews Read what people are saying about working here. Job details Job Type Part-time Full Job Description Application Instructions:
 For consideration please submit a CV and a statement of teaching philosophy.  These documents must be submitted together as one document through the resume upload field.
 Role and Responsibilities:
 University of the Sciences in Philadelphia is seeking part-time adjuncts in the area of Data Science and Analytics for the 2020 - 2021 academic year. Adjuncts will facilitate Data Science and Analytics courses online/asynchronously to Undergraduate Students in the USciences Online division. We are interested in innovative teaching approaches that complement the existing strengths of the University and contribute to the excellence of the learning experience and academic community.
 We are currently hiring adjunct instructors for 100% online, flexible programs and six term starts per year. Each term is eight weeks. Pay per Course: $2,200.00 (undergraduate level). Below is the schedule for 2021:
 Spring A 2021
 January 18 – March 14
 Spring B 2021
 March 15 – May 9
 Summer A 2021
 May 10 – July 4
 Summer B 2021
 July 5 – August 29
 Fall A 2021
 August 30 – October 24
 Fall B 2021
 October 25 – December 19
 This posting will remain active indefinitely to develop a pool of qualified applicants.
 Courses Available:
 Data Science and Analytics Introduction I
 Data Science and Analytics Introduction II
 Calculus
 Programming in R
 Visualization Strategies for Data Analytics
 Techniques for Business Data Analytics
 Introduction to Database Design
 Introduction to Algorithms and Data Structures
 Methods of Regression Analysis
 Fundamentals of Experiment Design and Analysis
 Data Mining
 Data Governance
 Advanced Statistics/Statistical Modeling
 Modeling and Predictive Analysis
 Data Science and Analytics Capstone
 Introduction to Epidemiology
 Essentials of Biostatistics
 Use of Big Data
 Programming SAS for Data Analysis
 Multivariate Analysis
 Introduction to Categorical Data Analysis
 Programming with Python
 Introduction to Survival Analysis
 Applied Mathematical Modeling
 Forecasting with Time Series Data
 Introduction to Stochastic Modeling
 Applied Numerical Analysis
 Applications in Information Security
 Artificial Intelligence
 Advanced SAS Programming
 Statistical Methods for Clinical Trials
 Introduction to Machine Learning
 Additional Expectations:
 Facilitate course via approved course plan/syllabus provided by USciences Online
 Adhere to all policies and expectations detailed in the USciences Online Adjunct Faculty Guide
 Knowledge, Skills, and Abilities Required:
 Master’s Degree in Data Science, Analytics, MBA or other-related field
 Subject matter expert in field with direct work experience
 Minimum 2-3 years of previous asynchronous, online teaching experience at the undergraduate level
 Experience with adult learners
 Access to computer: minimum computing requirements
 Comfortable with all aspects of online environment
 Flexible schedule to accommodate students in different time zones
 Active, ongoing engagement with all students to support learning
 1-week turnaround for grading online assignments
 24-hour turnaround for e-mails and responses to discussion board posts
 One-on-one consultations with students
 Willingness/availability to participate in ongoing online faculty development
 Adherence to ADA requirements for students with disabilities
 The finalist will be required to successfully pass a background check.
 The specific statements in this job description are not intended to be all-inclusive. They are typical criteria considered necessary to successfully perform the job.
 Preferred Qualifications:
 Doctoral degree in Data Science, Analytics, or related field with previous work experience in the field of Data Science and Analytics 
 
 
 At USciences we create a better world in many ways. We educate the next generation of leaders in healthcare and science, increase the world’s knowledge and improve the lives of people around the planet.
 
 
 USciences offers a wealth of opportunities for individuals seeking job, career and personal growth. Our campus community affords a wide range of faculty and staff positions that support our academic programs and students with many jobs similar to those found in private organizations.
 
 
